#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:18
msgid "October 27, 2019 by Extinction Rebellion"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:21
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><strong>This rebellion is by no means over</strong>: the past week has seen continued actions in <strong>Austria</strong>, <strong>The</strong> <strong>Netherlands</strong>, <strong>Hong Kong</strong>, <strong>Berlin</strong>, <strong>Sydney</strong>… as ever, more than we can count!\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:24
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>But for many of those reading, this week was the beginning of some well-earned rest, and the start of a reflection process.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>In this first of several <strong>retrospective issues</strong>, we \n"
"begin to look back together on the October Rebellion. We bring you \n"
"exclusive accounts that could only be articulated once the heat of \n"
"action had cooled a little.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://i2.wp.com/can2-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/data/000/336/231/original/berlinbamboo-min.jpeg?ssl=1\" alt=\"\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"><figcaption>Berlin rebels gather, featuring bamboo tripods</figcaption></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:39
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Undeniably, this Rebellion has seen XR <strong>step up across the world </strong>–\n"
" in terms of numbers, intensity, creativity, visibility, and more. We \n"
"saw a leap in the profile of those declaring their support for the \n"
"movement, with royalty, actors, journalists, and politicians using their\n"
" platforms to support XR, and some even facing arrest.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:45
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Rebels in many countries have <strong>developed their civil disobedience superpowers, </strong><strong>deploying new and creative tactic</strong><strong>s</strong>\n"
" – in this issue, we see how cross-national solidarity between rebels \n"
"has been used to the advantage of protests in Central Europe (Slovakia, \n"
"Czech Republic).\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:53
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>At the same time, we have seen the <strong>police step up its response to XR in sometimes shocking and brutal ways</strong>.\n"
" More than during the April Rebellion, it is as if brute force has been \n"
"mobilised in the service of shoring up the denial of climate and \n"
"ecological breakdown. Rebels seem undeterred however, even where they \n"
"are facing a public still largely unaware of the emergency (e.g. Czech \n"
"Republic, Italy).\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/can2-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/data/000/336/234/original/austriayouth-min.jpeg?ssl=1\" alt=\"\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"><figcaption>Austrian XR Youth take a dramatic stand</figcaption></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:64
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>The crucial process of <strong>holding to account those involved in the Rebellion has begun</strong> – and we don’t mean only the courageous arrestees: as we detail below, investigations into police excesses have started in <a href=\"https://www.brusselstimes.com/brussels/73091/probe-launched-into-unacceptable-violence-by-police-against-extinction-rebellion-activists/\">Belgium</a>\n"
" and in the UK. (In the UK an investigation is being conducted by Netpol\n"
" into excessive or discriminatory policing – they need eye-witness \n"
"statements to make their case please <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1H4r7xI3RaCgFbu8RhSjFa_0vI4BpgrHdxN2PrfJTrYY/edit?usp=sharing\">see here</a>\n"
" to help. If you’re not in the UK, but have had similar experiences, we \n"
"can only encourage you to contact legal networks to begin a similar \n"
"process!)\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:69
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Taking responsibility is not something we merely ask of others: the \n"
"time is also for apologies where these are felt to be necessary, for \n"
"example, the <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/ExtinctionRebellionBE/posts/543271136502664?__tn__=K-R\">heartfelt letter</a> from XR Belgium to members of the public and rebels caught up in the police response.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:71
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/can2-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/data/000/336/230/original/nhsdoctors-min.jpeg?ssl=1\" alt=\"\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:79
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>This retrospective newsletter features longer pieces that allow \n"
"rebels to share their experience of Rebellion more intimately. We are \n"
"struck by the raw humanity of rebel hunger strikers in <strong>Italy</strong>; the pain of the 14-year-old rebel from <strong>Slovakia</strong>,\n"
" brutally unglued by the police. The often touching photos lay bare a \n"
"whole spectrum of emotions – cheekiness, anger, puzzlement, \n"
"determination, playfulness. <strong>A reminder of our complex but ultimately common humanity</strong>.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:82
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>As these reflections begin to paint a fuller picture of the whirlwind that was Rebellion, it seems clear that <strong>what we have lost in innocence, we have gained in numbers, in determination, in skill and in solidarity.</strong>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:87
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><strong>Whatever the future may hold, this at least is clear: we are \n"
"now a community of truly international scale, and we will not stop until\n"
" we see the change we need.</strong>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

