#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:121
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<h3>This City Never Sleeps…\n"
"</h3>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:123
#, no-wrap
msgid "**OCT 20 – 25 \\| London, UK**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:126
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>October was massive for UK rebels. And for many who strained heart and sinew, the time has come for some well deserved rest. &nbsp;\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:129
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>But some push on, with <strong>inventive and powerful protests.</strong> &nbsp;\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:134
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>On Sunday, a small group of rebels<a href=\"https://rebellion.earth/2019/10/20/bp-portrait-awards-targeted-by-extinction-rebellion-activists-pour-crude-oil-over-naked-bodies-within-the-performance-crude-truth/\"> stripped off on the floor of the National Portrait Gallery</a>, while others<strong> poured fake oil over their naked bodies</strong>.\n"
" The gallery is the home of the BP Portrait Award, an exhibition funded \n"
"by oil and gas company ‘Beyond Petroleum’. The action highlighted the <strong>tragic destruction of life </strong>caused by the drills and spills of oil and gas companies like BP.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:136
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/CZ4E2R9FjRgtxXZvfT31yHCUvtid8Suu3hfQ4BNjQpiWcCZ6RMH2NIpCLuqZx9La8Lt6qizypzo5ZLwaNAv-Bz-mh8HUEGpn56pApDkAdQpHjo_cipFjCjJ3iljVJUKdhg72fh13\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:139
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>The following day, XR families and <a href=\"https://rebellion.earth/2019/10/21/teachers-scientists-parents-and-children-protest-at-department-for-education-to-demand-climate-truth-be-taught-in-schools-and-universities/\">educators called on the Department for Education</a> to ‘tell the truth’ and bring the climate emergency into the school curriculum. \n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:144
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>“<strong>Climate and ecological breakdown will define the life of every child alive today,</strong>”\n"
" said one rebel, “but it’s hard for them to take the issue seriously, \n"
"when it plays almost no part in the content of their education.”\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:146
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/QDcH975r90bzC6JtMiwAEhNx3fgXg76rvWSgBb_5yU9rgd9KRRXi2o99Pt0SvVSutESKpgQvmHFUDy-4kJ1LbSGeTHwnDErsu6iJBoUrpIVz3RJItywYkLV9jLRIPLTODsvqzs3E\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:149
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Little rebels brought a first ever <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/ExtinctionRebellionFamilies/posts/2491314754447548\">love-in to the Maritime Museum</a>. United in song, they stood in <strong>solidarity with families across the world already impacted by climate change</strong>, especially those in the global south. They also visited the new home of our Polly Higgins boat and honoured <a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2019/apr/22/polly-higgins-environmentalist-eradicating-ecocide-dies\">Polly’s fight to make ecocide a crime</a>.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:152
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Coming up this week in London, we have a Rebellion-inspired piano concert <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/457610948188230/\"><strong>‘Music From Our Times’</strong></a><strong> on Wed 30</strong> and a <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/547711839330320/\"><strong>Rebel Rave</strong></a><strong> on Fri 1st</strong> to raise money for legal aid for our brave arrestees (<a href=\"https://www.residentadvisor.net/events/1324937\">buy tickets here</a>).\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:157
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>If you can’t make these but feel like tying up some loose ends, a \n"
"debrief might be the thing you need – and the good news is, setting them\n"
" up just got a whole lot easier with this <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1uDaRbXqrcxCrpv2SG4Hgx73jwgyH0-FGBrqVJj0VTO0/edit\">guide</a>.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:160
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>We’d also like to encourage any rebels who were present in London to take a look at this <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1H4r7xI3RaCgFbu8RhSjFa_0vI4BpgrHdxN2PrfJTrYY/edit\">request from Netpol</a> – your statement could make a crucial difference in holding the Met to account for their actions earlier this month.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:162
#, no-wrap
msgid "<h2>Looking Back</h2>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:168
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><em>More happened in October than we could possibly report on. Each \n"
"country’s rebellion has its own joys and tribulations, its own unique \n"
"flavour. Read on to be seriously inspired!\n"
"    </em>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:171
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<h3>Shocks to Political Culture in France \n"
"</h3>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:173
#, no-wrap
msgid "**OCT 5-13 \\| Paris, France**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:178
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>The October Rebellion enabled XR to introduce itself to the French \n"
"media and political world, and to a large part of the population. This \n"
"spectacular introduction, intended to draw more rebels in, laid the \n"
"foundations for even more disruptive and dramatic actions in the future.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:180
#, no-wrap
msgid "</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:185
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>There is little doubt that this week of massive non-violent civil \n"
"disobedience created a shock wave in the country of ‘La Grande \n"
"Révolution.’  <strong>XR’s political aims and methods have struck many other protest movements in France as culturally strange</strong>, especially those on the radical left. \n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:187
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/mISUztohJsjVx99sYzSbZfJcIohkI0ElQe5glQOccMin_eLaLDz6uD5vTQJIEPr9iYCCi-kQD94TYsjAz66CVNCA0-e1yltsiTKrJcK-W01QpX3szG1u6jN4-sNr-maWMojNjumn\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:190
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><em>The sun sets after a fifth day of occupation in the centre of Paris</em>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:198
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>The difference between XR and more ‘traditional’ methods of protest \n"
"in the country, as well as its political message, drew critiques and \n"
"commendations from social and anti-authoritarian movements, public \n"
"commentators and intellectuals alike. These certainly deserve to be \n"
"heard and thought through, even if they indicate a certain reactionary \n"
"attitude within the French left itself. \n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:203
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>These criticisms could prove to help XR France mature, and provide a \n"
"fruitful disruption and inspiration for other social movements in the \n"
"country.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:208
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>In effect, the October Rebellion has offered an opportunity for both \n"
"XR France and movements such as the Yellow Vests to grow more impactful,\n"
" both in strategy and in their political aims and messaging. \n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:211
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Having begun to form alliances <a href=\"https://rebellion.earth/2019/10/08/xr-unchained-aaaand-were-off-international/?link_id=35&amp;can_id=54b822cf8e46ca1da066a06d60944eb7&amp;source=email-rebel-daily-1-the-sun-rises-on-a-new-wave-of-rebellion&amp;email_referrer=email_636120&amp;email_subject=rebel-daily-1-the-sun-rises-on-a-new-wave-of-rebellion\">in the first days of the rebellion</a>, <strong>now is the time to reflect on how to collaborate more successfully with one another moving forward</strong>.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:213
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/GjDuY6ttsQmC0T_VunKFwa1-ZBD-8BJrMcYzO4yMfW2iFnbdNFfTgGlzQcemVoVBwtvp-IkmB6CNpFds9kQ_hKxKnXc_EskFIgJXkMexIbKKfNLvtZgKOkUD1IUMuaSVNtdgy4we\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:216
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><em>On October 5th, XR co-occupied a Parisian Shopping Centre with the Yellow Vests and other groups</em>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:221
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>In the face of the task ahead of us, we might together concede that \n"
"we will need a full spectrum of tactics to reach our shared goal: that \n"
"is, <strong>to dismantle the toxic structures which are the source of this generation’s emergency</strong>. \n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:224
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Read a full analysis and response to criticisms of the French Rebellion <a href=\"https://rebellion.earth/2019/10/25/shocks-to-political-culture-in-france/\">here</a>.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:227
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<h3>The Czech Rebellion: Battered, Bruised, but Never Knocked Out\n"
"</h3>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:229
#, no-wrap
msgid "**OCT 7-12 \\| Prague, Czech Republic**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:231
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/157LFidznPkyF5QwVbUZilwQTtUG7RuP1tSTJVj1iIAVEWZrFmUSGOF1kw2ZmrsHohWEHN-Z0nk01Dq4gA81io7j4sG74C01I0KSUxWmtHuWyvhJE8kmsZ74i8byEqFhSmXP-gdG\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:234
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><em>Potential new recruits at ‘Fragile Hope’, an XR Prague Parents event</em>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:237
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Saturday 12th marked the final day of a <strong>week-long rebellion </strong>for XR Czechia, and the day was to hold<strong> two of their most audacious actions</strong>.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:240
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Rebels took over Wenceslas Square, one of Prague’s busiest, to hold a<strong> ‘Saturday Festival’</strong> full of live music, theatre, and workshops about the climate and ecological crisis. Meanwhile, on an adjacent highway, around <strong>200 rebels formed a blockade</strong> to stop the capital’s afternoon traffic. At least eight rebels glued themselves to the road.<br>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:243
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Police managed to clear the blockade in under 15 minutes, but they did so <strong>brutally</strong>. It resulted in one woman being <strong>scalded </strong>with hot water (which police believed would dissolve the glue), another woman suffering <strong>significant bruising</strong> as she was hauled away.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:246
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>And a 14-year-old girl having<strong> skin ripped away from her hand</strong>. She was glued to another rebel and the police, who appeared <strong>unprepared and seemingly unaware of the practice,</strong> simply tore them apart.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:248
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/BE1--ObcufNusHBzjHm_mMIYqNmDuWgA7X1p6TnMV9pjmSMANIl1PUQnn_nwVCQtXS9bITUzR3RAh1CVbLGQMyXlh2-X71UlWuIAhpfyCIeuuduys_6g6MkPDUGL4g_egavdZatT\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:251
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><em>The 14 year old girl whose glued hand was torn free (Photo: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pg/zewlakkaktivistckefoto\">Petr Zewlakk Vrabec</a>)</em>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:256
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>As <strong>she cried, a rebel medic tried to help her</strong> but \n"
"the police had already formed a cordon around the road and wouldn’t let \n"
"anyone through. ‘We have our own medics,’ was the police response.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:261
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>The police medics did eventually arrive and were seriously alarmed, \n"
"mistakenly believing the girl’s hand was dissolving from chemicals in \n"
"the glue. She was <strong>rushed to hospital in an ambulance,</strong> her mother by her side.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:264
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>On the journey, the girl was given a misdemeanour citation and was released a few hours later.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:266
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/J1FS10WBpt90S2vd4BcLuY5TvVEhRGo6V9Ti2komN5HggeUCF_E_KqtjsiLK7h4SWfVr4qAQHNtWjXloSLWMW9gTrDV2fpBz_i4lUyWNcUgBLRMCh4LILEbLTukwB-iVS7wJmU4d\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:269
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><em>Police held the blockade rebels for five and a half hours</em>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:275
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Most rebels were kept for far longer. There were <strong>130 arrests in all</strong>,\n"
" and the police seemed totally at a loss with how to deal with so many. \n"
"They decided to process all of them, including the minors and the \n"
"injured, in an impromptu holding area by the road.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:281
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Those rebels whose ID cards had already been registered by the police\n"
" after previous actions were arrested and bussed to the local police \n"
"station. Whilst they were ultimately released later that night, they are\n"
" <strong>likely to face substantial fines</strong>.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:287
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Those rebels whose IDs showed no previous XR activity were cautioned \n"
"and eventually released after a five-and-a-half-hour wait on the \n"
"roadside. They sang and chanted throughout the night to keep their \n"
"spirits high.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:289
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/5AwSmU4L0BzdnJSxMohGP_pS5byjw0_M5g3NoUcLK-iV4_wr02ykU9EBDMI6cs-SIJ-JsiQATITptoF4EihP1kdnYhfQ8dk_HXAtL9NmFVq3HkZkfC3Rzpzc4WFBCx0jez2aMSA6\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:292
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><em>A road swarm meets with anger on the streets of Prague</em>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:295
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>XR Czech Republic is spearheaded by a <strong>loving group of around 400 dedicated activists.</strong> Generally speaking, though, public opinion is not with them — in part because of a <strong>hostile corporate media </strong>that misreports actions and sidelines the climate crisis entirely.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:298
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Through their Saturday Festival and other events across the week, Czech rebels have sought to recruit a new wave of rebels; <strong>but they also know that to change this nation’s mindset, they have a lot of work ahead.</strong>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:301
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<h3>Slovakia’s Rebellion: History Quietly in the Making\n"
"</h3>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:303
#, no-wrap
msgid "**OCT 7-12 \\| Bratislava, Slovakia, and Prague, Czech Republic**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:305
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/cen4uOx6339mFCDWa1DZU0OX9KuMYEc0ix4TnEU-iG9Zhx3LFxWvrGDkjk8frsNBIs739fT1oi6FmkOG4yjtFbTNP_F-uqamkJVKuvN07XXx-ePi8PkCWIreX0KKR1-ZUE8817H1\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:308
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><em>The first ‘swarm’ in the history of Slovakia</em>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:313
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>It is the morning of Monday 7th October, the first day of rebellion \n"
"for so many across the world. Twenty Slovak rebels walked in single file\n"
" across a zebra crossing on a street outside the <strong>Ministry of Economic Affairs in Bratislava</strong>.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:316
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>But rather than cross the street, they blocked it. Two big hand-painted XR banners were unfurled to face the waiting traffic.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:323
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>People in their cars looked bemused, unsure about what was going on. A\n"
" bus driver started to get angry, inching his large vehicle closer to \n"
"the rebels, gesturing and shouting from behind the glass. Thankfully the\n"
" agreed seven-minute wait was up before things could get violent, and \n"
"the rebels part like waves.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:327
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>The traffic returns to its normal flow, and no police arrived. It is \n"
"as if nothing had happened. But the beaming rebels know differently. \n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:330
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>This was their first-ever direct action. It was Slovakia’s first-ever swarm. <strong>This was seven minutes of history.</strong>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:336
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Later that day, the rebels notified Slovakia’s national media about \n"
"this milestone. They also hosted a seminar about how to turn kitchen and\n"
" bathroom household waste into garden compost. The press interest was \n"
"muted however: the next morning, <strong>only one newspaper ran the story.</strong>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:341
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>XR Slovakia is only a few months old and its membership is still \n"
"modest in size. In spite of this, actions came thick and fast during \n"
"Rebellion Week. On Wednesday 9th a group of <strong>seventy cyclists rode through Bratislava, passing various Ministries and gridlocking traffic</strong>. Again the police did not impose, and no one was arrested.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:343
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/_zv5-jMKYSVntlKf8d-U_yYke5uc60SHh1wJjysToPBLievYGFYKv6Xg192w9JlyIm3Ns_DSnxzm8WKjZYjpOFcIsbd-UarPLRVveG8Kp7IprvweZy7stnWt4Ee-J_tEYkN8OsEi\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:346
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><em>Three Slovak women on the front line of the rebel blockade in Prague</em>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:348
#, no-wrap
msgid "<p>The next day, Thursday 10th, <strong>twelve rebels took a trip to Prague to join their Czech sisters and brothers</strong>. All were part of the Saturday blockade that saw the Czech police kettle nearly 200 rebels, injuring two women and a teenage girl in the  process. </p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:356
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>The Slovaks’ foreign status actually helped them in this instance. \n"
"The added bureaucracy involved in processing their foreign ID cards \n"
"meant that the overstretched Czech police were never going to arrest \n"
"them. Instead, the visitors spent their last night on the roadside, \n"
"chanting with their Czech comrades for the five and a half hours it took\n"
" for the police to release them.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:358
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/ari_XKAj2MJWlWdEgoaLRKRQf020zTd4wwzX5B64pZOYDYlHNxTOHVnR1_J3NhxDrxRM6ZEdbV6LKKVsPeSVIjYNmLBngYKNm6i5wxnSwRLhob4ruzW_IaByu4ydsbVig755rCG7\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:361
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><em>XR Slovakia performed a funeral march during the global strike called for by ‘Fridays for Future’</em>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:364
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<h3>The Rome Rebellion: Bikes, Lies, and Videotape\n"
"</h3>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:366
#, no-wrap
msgid "**OCT 7-13 \\| Rome, Italy**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:368
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/NWCe4M6pF-OID1j4z2H5uopg5nZ4WGLGAqkx5xta65Lpm9nC_F1qbYyXnMoaUmRmsP8442V6xioo8cGIb7sJ9VGCiz88xaRUyaIUgil1XYnfgQ5WB5v-PUxhSL4dZ_utDravn45G\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:371
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><em>Critical Mass passes through Piazza Venezia</em>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:374
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Asked for her favourite action of the week, a rebel from the Rome media team smiles and answers quickly: ‘The Critical Mass. <strong>A hundred and fifty of us riding bikes</strong> through the centre of the city, blocking traffic for three hours’.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:379
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Italian police knew the starting point of the action and followed the\n"
" swarm of bicycles in two big trucks as the riders cut through red \n"
"lights and <strong>brought the city streets to a standstill</strong>. But there were no arrests. In fact, <strong>there have never been any arrests of rebels in Italy.</strong>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:384
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>‘The police just video-record our faces,’ says the rebel from Rome. \n"
"‘Throughout the week, over the course of seven major actions, the police\n"
" have just watched and waited and filmed everyone.’\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:386
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/GSyNnd6j3USL-Qr-MUQgob4EcKxvHAwzJynYdMvBRVlraZVS3gdGQRAtFZhswaR9SuPZq9rG914i44wPo7RGJxnKGDS0mYKtRA1ncD1Dn0ifTafhfglH4q6HP7VEOwJR9-31Nz98\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:389
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><em>Italian rebel on day six of his hunger strike</em>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:392
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>A public endorsement from <strong>Michael Stipe, lead singer of REM</strong>, visiting Rome for an art convention, gained press coverage but it was the <strong>rebel hunger strikers</strong> who sat in a square outside the Italian Parliament which drew the most media attention.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:398
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Of the fifteen who started, ten hunger strikers made it through the \n"
"whole week. Three were forced to end their strike because of health \n"
"fears. But thanks to a couple of supportive MEPs, the hunger strikers \n"
"were visited by Italy’s Environment Minister, Sergio Costa.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:403
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>The senior politician listened to the hunger strikers, but only for a\n"
" minute or so. He had a more important agenda for this meeting: turning \n"
"to the assembled press and lauding his<strong> ‘emergency bill about the climate’</strong>, a bill that had passed into Italian law only the day before.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:405
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/Q8AN9JTjV3BxWiMvRJ016s38SnpeOZAUvMy8O02rrumCdkIcq5IJ1jXTCfIp0pTdAtFvMouKTdOnXUJBIp-uiAXnbushFQupYgh0SKNWO-D_T2DOxOFTRHVbYb8RrClPAtxpGEeR\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:408
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><em>Rebel hunger strikers outside Montecitorio Palace, the Italian parliament</em>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:414
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Like so many similar bills which have been lauded by governments \n"
"around the world, the substance did not match the title. While the bill \n"
"introduces measures to tackle plastic use and offers financial \n"
"incentives for drivers of older model cars to upgrade it remains silent <strong>on the issues of carbon emissions, fossil fuel usage and air travel.</strong> The phrase ‘fiddling while Rome burns’ has rarely been more apt. &nbsp;\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:416
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/bwjT4Z9TxC8k1FLe1PiDw4XM1ES1isXlqvzaCWoh2M8lqCLXN8w8D0FVETdIoGXfy8uK_udPGDtmZY6Cg_J-xnlixIsUvf7UsHLPL1FWXM6aKWzAIawm1P2BZnBlsBa0Xqow7LFo\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:419
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><em>Environment Minister Sergio Costa meets the hunger strikers</em>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:422
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>It was a real achievement that the hunger strikers got any press coverage at all. <strong>Mostly, the Italian media has ignored the climate and ecological crisis</strong>, and totally ignored Extinction Rebellion’s efforts to highlight it.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:425
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><strong>The vast majority of people in Italy don’t know that there is a climate problem, let alone its true scale.</strong> During the actions in the capital, the most supportive passers-by were tourists.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:432
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>XR Italy is comprised of only a couple of hundred dedicated rebel hearts, but<strong> the week of actions has done wonders</strong>,\n"
" both in terms of the skills and systems that have been passed on \n"
"through workshops, and the bonds that have been created through direct \n"
"actions. Trust and camaraderie has grown strong between these rebellious\n"
" Romans, and <strong>new chapters are now springing up daily</strong> around the country.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:435
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>One thing is for sure. The Italian police will be needing to record more videos.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:438
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<h3>Brussels Revisited\n"
"</h3>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:440
#, no-wrap
msgid "**OCT 12-13 \\| Brussels, Belgium**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:442
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/HMCUccZTZlvF-DJU7xjVAQm81S7d6m7VDn4SaPKQANhDNeNjVICTxPZDD4KoQGR4smmaFDjEvHax0NwtuICYYQlinUKIDFZfNEpOetScNXluoDp7xOw_NV2psTYaDkxJbHKU3SKc\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:445
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Many of us were shocked by the events in Belgium on Saturday 12th, when<strong> over 400 peaceful rebels were savagely beaten, soaked, pepper-sprayed, and arrested</strong> on their first day of protest.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:448
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Authorities in Brussels have since <a href=\"https://www.brusselstimes.com/brussels/73091/probe-launched-into-unacceptable-violence-by-police-against-extinction-rebellion-activists/\">opened up an inquiry</a> exploring the <strong>unlawful conduct of the police</strong>. A total of four separate<a href=\"https://www.vrt.be/vrtnws/en/2019/10/22/four-disciplinary-investigations-into-alleged-police-brutality-a/\"> disciplinary investigations</a> have been launched to address the potential use of <strong>excessive force and unacceptable violence</strong>. \n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:451
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Meanwhile, we spoke to a rebel on the ground about his experience of the night: <strong>‘It’s hard to describe what it’s like to be hit in the face by pepper-spray.</strong> <strong>The best comparison I can think of, is hell</strong>. Everything burns and you feel completely disoriented. Out of this world. You can’t see, or smell, or even breathe.’\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:454
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>‘<strong>It’s like someone has poured a cocktail of tabasco and bleach down your throat. </strong>And there’s nothing you can do. Water makes it worse. You just have to wait it out.’\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:456
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/jFytlW27Q8aB-r5SjdjW_Pvc9aO2i61GnIMn8_8ZDne6uCFZmOghtsiJI6S4nijVa0tQvBX8a23Avouow0F6yDflRzt9o4dzeCDBDkWumP8h3brUnlqKaWy29OF66TPSDHFGeHss\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:461
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Rest assured, Extinction Rebellion will be paying very close \n"
"attention to the results of the police enquiry. On Tuesday 15th, XR \n"
"spokesperson <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/watch/?v=517045218851015\"><strong>Linde Polfliet appeared on national television channel VRT</strong></a>to discuss our <strong>peaceful values </strong>and denounce the <strong>criminal actions</strong> of the police.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:464
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>XR Belgium have also released a <strong>heartfelt statement </strong>addressing ‘the negligent and stupid <strong>brutality of the illegal police action </strong>that ruined a truly beautiful and inspiring afternoon of citizen cooperation’.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:467
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>The statement generously apologises to all XR members and members of the public who were caught up in ‘<strong>the nightmare </strong>that we all experienced.’ It celebrates the<strong> indomitable spirit </strong>of those who made the stand and ends with a reminder that: <strong>‘the system, of which we are part of, is afraid</strong>. It does not know what to do (…) It needs our help to go forward. <strong>It needs us.’</strong>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:470
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>You can read the statement in full <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/10iP49D8fbL2WCN97Hfone2vGBxQyZM6O/view?usp=sharing\">here</a>.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:473
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><strong>Deeds not Words</strong><br>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:476
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><em>An overview of police response to the October Rebellion, in London and around the world.</em>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:483
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Our <strong>October Rebellion </strong>received many different \n"
"responses: energy and excitement from new rebels across the world, love \n"
"and community with returning rebels, curiosity from passersby, some \n"
"grumbles from grumpy commuters in a rush, but also a new level of \n"
"intimidation and aggression from the police.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:489
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>In London, <a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2019/oct/05/london-police-arrest-extinction-rebellion-activists-in-advance-of-environment-protest\">police swooped in before the rebellion even began</a>, raiding a storage space, confiscating equipment, including<strong> <a href=\"https://rebellion.earth/2019/10/05/you-cant-confiscate-an-idea/\">dangerous pink pillows</a></strong>\n"
" and making arrests. Over the following days, police continued with \n"
"arrests and confiscated all manner of items from rebels, including food \n"
"and tents. \n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:491
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/DaYoXzvv---j351CF_sIyWWaoWT9dWWa9_oqIHpolSWZseO7ksUadxAXa3LzjgetjdITXJTorJFqlVV3PO3D5GvK_zTidYqVkLBzln8XVpmf5dli3-F7q01Xh-vclgBPJIj6WUwy\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:497
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>In true rebellious spirit, <strong>pink pillows popped up </strong>all\n"
" over London and the Rebellion was on again. Rebels continued to defy \n"
"police aggression, even when it hit an all time low with police \n"
"targeting more vulnerable rebels by<strong> confiscating wheelchairs and equipment supporting disabled rebels</strong> to protest.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:500
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>But as the rebel spirit couldn’t be knocked down, the police responded with increasingly draconian measures <strong>curtailing the right to protest</strong>; initially by restricting protest to Trafalgar Square and then <strong>banning all XR protests from London</strong>.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:505
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Greta <a href=\"https://twitter.com/GretaThunberg/status/1184188303295336448\">tweeted</a>:\n"
" ‘If standing up against the climate and ecological breakdown and for \n"
"humanity is against the rules then the rules must be broken’.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:512
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>The disproportionate <strong>London-wide ban on XR protests</strong> backfired. Galvanising support from those who recognised how dangerous a development this was, including <strong>Amnesty International</strong> who called the ban<a href=\"https://www.amnesty.org.uk/press-releases/extinction-rebellion-blanket-ban-chilling-and-unlawful\">chilling and unlawful</a>’. Green Party Co-Leader <strong>Jonathan Bartley</strong> and journalist <strong>George Monbiot</strong>\n"
" were amongst those arrested the following day for deliberately defying \n"
"it. The legality of the ban is now being challenged in the High Court, \n"
"while Netpol is launching a parliamentary report which you can help with\n"
" by <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1H4r7xI3RaCgFbu8RhSjFa_0vI4BpgrHdxN2PrfJTrYY/edit\">offering a statement</a>.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:514
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/MNl_goT2q4dSK3S5DHIUYdRtlCPrso8cyfGrZZykE8I_gazqoaVtBYJGdGxCpg2p29eMGeRUU9e3DkkNoilG8IzuNq3Bv9YcrK1myuXnrKAM4H2JHoNuZSw2x9YkUeJXl5lHG2vS\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:519
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Unfortunately the UK hasn’t been the only place where, instead of \n"
"acting on the climate and ecological emergency, politicians have instead\n"
" turned on peaceful protest. \n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:522
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>In Australia, the <strong>Queensland parliament</strong> criminalised locking devices and extended <a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2019/oct/24/queensland-parliament-passes-laws-to-crack-down-on-climate-protesters\">police powers</a>, shortly after Australian police faced criticism for their use of strip searches and imposition of extreme <a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2019/oct/09/absurd-bail-conditions-prevent-extinction-rebellion-protesters-going-near-other-members\">bail conditions</a>.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:527
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>Use of pain compliance techniques against peaceful earth protectors \n"
"was reported in Germany and Spain, while non-violent protest in Brussels\n"
" was met with police <strong>violence far beyond anything experienced before</strong>. \n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:529
#, no-wrap
msgid "<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/4UCcDrMpP5ZAHmFaVcHfaryOUnS-x7f-E5EDFBFLg72uH79_T3ahySYK4H8tBvilmFdsNMjJcPdlsEuPRZLitSpgWqsl6GPU9hvQafoqzL0_ZXQAKxI4RQ9rpHOXJN3Jc-5U1T6Q\" alt=\"\"></figure>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:532
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>These extreme responses to peaceful action show that <strong>those in power are running scared and panicking</strong>. Attempts to ignore and ridicule XR have failed and they recognise the force of change we now represent. \n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:536
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>The way forward doesn’t require further draconian steps on a path \n"
"towards a police state with no civil liberties; all that is needed, is <strong>taking action on the climate and ecological emergency</strong>.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

