#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:555
#, no-wrap
msgid "<strong>Alice, 18</strong>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:558
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>‘I don’t think enough is being done. This feels like a huge joke or something, a nightmare, <strong>but it’s not. It’s the reality. </strong><strong>I just wanted to try anything I can to change this horrible reality.</strong> I think I’d regret not doing anything.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:564
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>I think here (the City of London) is the right place to do it. I \n"
"study Economics and I feel so strongly that something has to change. The\n"
" banks should be diverting resources to renewable projects which will \n"
"create jobs. They’re just not doing that, <strong>they’re stuck in their short-termism and their quarterly reports and shareholder values and things</strong>.\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:569
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>It’s always been really hard for me because I’m an overseas student \n"
"and I used to fly a lot. I think that if I believe that it is such a \n"
"catastrophe then why am I still flying? So<strong> I’ve stopped flying and I’m looking at alternatives such as trains back to Hong Kong. </strong>\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2019-10-27-newsletter-30.md:576
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>I’m consuming so much less now and I’ve realised that makes me a \n"
"happier person. I grew up in a concrete jungle and I’ve always been \n"
"taught that shopping is fun, but I never really took a moment to \n"
"consider where my happiness comes from. I think that would be true for a\n"
" lot of people, <strong>it’s just the culture that we grew up in</strong>.’\n"
"</p>\n"
msgstr ""

